1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
It was Ramadan—at <i>suhoor</i> we
got <i>samoon</i> [finger roll] and tahini

2
00:00:05,458 --> 00:00:07,041
The <i>samoon</i> bread was stale

3
00:00:07,958 --> 00:00:10,250
It crumbled when you held it

4
00:00:11,250 --> 00:00:12,958
And they brought the tahini dip

5
00:00:14,333 --> 00:00:15,500
And a pot of tea

6
00:00:16,458 --> 00:00:19,000
Everyone ate <i>suhoor</i>,
prayed, and slept

7
00:00:19,958 --> 00:00:23,875
At <i>iftar</i> they brought soup

8
00:00:24,458 --> 00:00:26,416
Or rice, or bulgur

9
00:00:26,791 --> 00:00:27,833
That's the food

10
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:30,250
Interviewer: And was everyone forced to fast?
Witness: Yes

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:32,833
Anyone who didn't
fast was punished

12
00:00:33,583 --> 00:00:35,041
And anyone who didn't pray too

13
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:38,250
Even long pants got you punished

14
00:00:39,250 --> 00:00:41,416
Interviewer: Punished while inside the cell?
Witness: Yes

15
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:50,875
Interviewer: Were the <i>iftar</i>
and <i>suhoor</i> meals in Ramadan

16
00:00:50,916 --> 00:00:52,916
Enough and filling?

17
00:00:54,458 --> 00:00:58,125
Half the people didn't eat
because it wasn't enough

18
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:03,208
They brought a small
pot for 70 to 80 people

19
00:01:03,250 --> 00:01:04,041
So who would it be enough for?

20
00:01:04,666 --> 00:01:06,208
It isn't only one or two people

21
00:01:07,333 --> 00:01:09,958
Interviewer: Seventy to eighty people inside each room?
Witness: Yes

22
00:01:10,708 --> 00:01:11,666
So who would it be enough for?

23
00:01:12,375 --> 00:01:16,125
They brought a small pot, threw it by the
door, turned their backs, and walked away

24
00:01:17,500 --> 00:01:20,416
From their own food and drink

25
00:01:21,083 --> 00:01:25,916
Interviewer: When you were inside the room,
you mentioned there were many jars of tahini

26
00:01:26,041 --> 00:01:29,458
Were all the jars in your room

27
00:01:29,500 --> 00:01:34,041
They used to
bring five to six jars

28
00:01:34,541 --> 00:01:35,708
And distribute them to the rooms

29
00:01:37,041 --> 00:01:41,791
So whoever got hungry
would take some and eat

30
00:01:42,625 --> 00:01:48,041
And when it was time for
iftar and they brought the food

31
00:01:48,958 --> 00:01:50,750
They would eat,
finish, and then sit

32
00:01:50,750 --> 00:01:54,125
And at night, whoever
was hungry or hadn't eaten

33
00:01:54,541 --> 00:01:56,625
Would eat tahini,
<i>samoon</i>, and tea

34
00:01:59,583 --> 00:02:03,458
Interviewer: Was the food
they brought clean and healthy?

35
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:05,416
Or was it, for
example, old and stale?

36
00:02:06,375 --> 00:02:09,666
It was the leftovers
of their own food

37
00:02:10,208 --> 00:02:12,875
From what they ate themselves

38
00:02:13,916 --> 00:02:15,791
They brought the
leftovers up to us

39
00:02:16,625 --> 00:02:21,458
Interviewer: Did you notice any
obvious diseases among the prisoners?

40
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:25,708
They didn’t complain, but did
you see anyone with itching or lice?

41
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:31,791
Anyone in pain or suffering
from an illness, like a fever

42
00:02:33,083 --> 00:02:37,333
No, there was no illness at
all, no scabies or anything else

43
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:42,083
Interviewer: Was there any medical care for you?
Witness: No

44
00:02:42,125 --> 00:02:43,583
There was absolutely
no medical care

45
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:51,958
Interviewer: If you asked
for more food or health care

46
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,166
Or for clean water

47
00:02:54,166 --> 00:02:56,166
Interviewer: Did they respond to you?
Witness: No

48
00:02:57,208 --> 00:03:00,333
We drank water from the toilets

49
00:03:01,041 --> 00:03:03,541
We filled it and
drank from there
